1:1 COMMENT "# io_textwriter.z -- string-oriented writes through a buffered sink."
1:69 EOL "\n"
2:1 COMMENT "#"
2:2 EOL "\n"
3:1 COMMENT "# Three-layer stack, each with its own path-scoped lock:"
3:57 EOL "\n"
4:1 COMMENT "#"
4:2 EOL "\n"
5:1 COMMENT "#   io.open -> file"
5:20 EOL "\n"
6:1 COMMENT "#   io.bufwriter.create -> holds the file via writer.lock"
6:58 EOL "\n"
7:1 COMMENT "#   io.textwriter.create -> holds the bufwriter via bufwriter.lock"
7:67 EOL "\n"
8:1 COMMENT "#"
8:2 EOL "\n"
9:1 COMMENT "# While tw is alive, bw cannot be flushed directly (its lock is"
9:64 EOL "\n"
10:1 COMMENT "# held by tw); while bw is alive, the underlying file cannot be"
10:64 EOL "\n"
11:1 COMMENT "# written directly. RAII: scope exit runs destructors in reverse"
11:65 EOL "\n"
12:1 COMMENT "# order, but none of them auto-flush -- call tw.flush explicitly."
12:66 EOL "\n"
13:1 EOL "\n"
